At the time of its original description, Auroriana florianensis was first suggested by Herbin (2012) to be unique among Mimallonidae and possibly belonging to a new genus. Despite this opinion, with which we agree, Herbin placed this species in the "catch-all" genus Cicinnus , which is currently being used to subsume many newly described taxa that show no obvious generic associations ( Herbin 2012 , 2015 , Herbin and Mielke 2014 ,
Herbin and Monzon 2015
).
